verses.roman:
āste-vyaste purī-gosāñi prabhu āge gelā
anunaya kari' prabhure ghare vasāilā

synonyms: āste-vyaste—with great haste; purī-gosāñi—Paramānanda Purī; prabhu āge—in front of Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; gelā—went; anunaya kari'-with great humility; prabhure—Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; ghare—in His room; vasāilā—got to sit down.
translation: In great haste Paramānanda Purī Gosāñi went before Him and with great humility persuaded Him to sit down in His own room.
